<inglise> Decision on Measures Concerning the Possible Negative Effects of the </inglise>
<eesti> vl36 RT II 1999, 22, 123 </eesti>
<inglise> Reform Programme on Least-Developed and Net Food-Importing Developing Countries </inglise>
<eesti> OTSUS MEETMETE KOHTA, MIS PUUDUTAVAD REFORMIPROGRAMMI V&Otilde;IMALIKKE NEGATIIVSEID M&Otilde;JUSID V&Auml;HIMARENENUD MAADELE JA TOIDUAINETE PUHASIMPORDIGA ARENGUMAADELE </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Ministers recognize that the progressive implementation of the results of the Uruguay Round as a whole will generate increasing opportunities for trade expansion and economic growth to the benefit of all participants. </inglise>
<eesti> Ministrid t&otilde;devad, et Uruguay vooru tulemuste j&auml;rkj&auml;rguline rakendamine tervikuna loob suurenevaid v&otilde;imalusi kaubanduse laiendamiseks ja majanduskasvuks k&otilde;ikide osalejate kasuks. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Ministers recognize that during the reform programme leading to greater liberalization of trade in agriculture least-developed and net food-importing developing countries may experience negative effects in terms of the availability of adequate supplies of basic foodstuffs from external sources on reasonable terms and conditions, including short-term difficulties in financing normal levels of commercial imports of basic foodstuffs. </inglise>
<eesti> Ministrid tunnistavad, et p&otilde;llumajanduskaubanduse suuremale liberaliseerimisele viiva reformiprogrammi jooksul v&otilde;ivad v&auml;himarenenud maad ja toiduainete puhasimpordiga arengumaad kogeda negatiivseid m&otilde;jusid v&auml;lisallikatest piisavas koguses ja m&otilde;istlikel tingimustel p&otilde;hitoiduainete k&auml;ttesaamisel, sealhulgas l&uuml;hiajalisi raskusi p&otilde;hitoiduainete tavalise kaubandusliku impordi finantseerimisel. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Ministers accordingly agree to establish appropriate mechanisms to ensure that the implementation of the results of the Uruguay Round on trade in agriculture does not adversely affect the availability of food aid at a level which is sufficient to continue to provide assistance in meeting the food needs of developing countries, especially least-developed and net food-importing developing countries. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt sellele lepivad ministrid kokku kehtestada asjakohane mehhanism tagamaks, et Uruguay vooru tulemuste rakendamine p&otilde;llumajanduskaubanduses ei m&otilde;jutaks ebasoodsalt toiduabi k&auml;ttesaadavust tasemel, millest piisab abistamise j&auml;tkamiseks, et rahuldada arengumaade, eriti v&auml;himarenenud maade ja toiduainete puhasimpordiga arengumaade toiduvajadusi. </eesti>
<inglise> To this end Ministers agree: </inglise>
<eesti> Sel eesm&auml;rgil lepivad ministrid kokku: </eesti>
<inglise> (i) to review the level of food aid established periodically by the Committee on Food Aid under the Food Aid Convention 1986 and to initiate negotiations in the appropriate forum to establish a level of food aid commitments sufficient to meet the legitimate needs of developing countries during the reform programme; </inglise>
<eesti> i) vaadata l&auml;bi toiduabi komitee poolt 1986. aasta toiduabi konventsiooni alusel regulaarselt kehtestatud toiduabi tase ja alustada asjakohasel foorumil l&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimisi kehtestamaks toiduabi kohustuste tase, mis on piisav arengumaade &otilde;igustatud vajaduste rahuldamiseks reformiprogrammi ajal; </eesti>
<inglise> (ii) to adopt guidelines to ensure that an increasing proportion of basic foodstuffs is provided to least-developed and net food-importing developing countries in fully grant form and/or on appropriate concessional terms in line with Article IV of the Food Aid Convention 1986; </inglise>
<eesti> ii) v&otilde;tta vastu juhend tagamaks, et endisest suurem osa p&otilde;hitoiduaineid antakse v&auml;himarenenud maadele ja toiduainete puhasimpordiga arengumaadele t&auml;ieliku annetusena ja/v&otilde;i sobivatel soodustingimustel vastavalt 1986. aasta toiduabi konventsiooni IV artiklile; </eesti>
<inglise> (iii) to give full consideration in the context of their aid programmes to requests for the provision of technical and financial assistance to least-developed and net food-importing developing countries to improve their agricultural productivity and infrastructure. </inglise>
<eesti> iii) p&ouml;&ouml;rata seoses abiprogrammidega t&auml;it t&auml;helepanu taotlustele anda tehnilist ja finantsabi v&auml;himarenenud maadele ja toiduainete puhasimpordiga arengumaadele nende p&otilde;llumajanduse tootlikkuse ja infrastruktuuri parandamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> Ministers further agree to ensure that any agreement relating to agricultural export credits makes appropriate provision for differential treatment in favour of least-developed and net food-importing developing countries. </inglise>
<eesti> Edasi lepivad ministrid kokku tagada, et p&otilde;llumajanduslike ekspordikrediitidega seotud mis tahes lepingus on asjakohane s&auml;te diferentseeritud re&zcaron;iimi kohta v&auml;himarenenud maade ja toiduainete puhasimpordiga arengumaade kasuks. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> Ministers recognize that as a result of the Uruguay Round certain developing countries may experience short-term difficulties in financing normal levels of commercial imports and that these countries may be eligible to draw on the resources of international financial institutions under existing facilities, or such facilities as may be established, in the context of adjustment programmes, in order to address such financing difficulties. </inglise>
<eesti> Ministrid tunnistavad, et Uruguay vooru tulemusena v&otilde;ivad teatud arengumaad kogeda l&uuml;hiajalisi raskusi normaaltasemega kaubandusliku impordi finantseerimisel ja et need maad v&otilde;ivad olla &otilde;igustatud kasutama rahvusvaheliste finantsinstitutsioonide vahendeid olemasolevate soodustuste v&otilde;i kohandamisprogrammidega seotud finantsraskustest jagusaamiseks kehtestatavate soodustuste alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> In this regard Ministers take note of paragraph 37 of the report of the Director-General to the CONTRACTING PARTIES to GATT 1947 on his consultations with the Managing Director of the International Monetary Fund and the President of the World Bank (MTN. GNG/NG14/W/35). </inglise>
<eesti> Selles suhtes v&otilde;tavad ministrid arvesse GATT 1947 LEPINGUOSALISTE peadirektori ettekande punkti 37 tema konsultatsioonide kohta Rahvusvahelise Valuutafondi tegevdirektori ja Maailmapanga presidendiga (MTN.GNG/NG14/W/35). </eesti>
<inglise> 6. </inglise>
<eesti> 6. </eesti>
<inglise> The provisions of this Decision will be subject to regular review by the Ministerial Conference, and the follow-up to this Decision shall be monitored, as appropriate, by the Committee on Agriculture. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva otsuse s&auml;tted vaatab regulaarselt l&auml;bi ministrite konverents ja selle otsuse j&auml;rgimist kontrollib asjakohaselt p&otilde;llumajanduskomitee. </eesti>
 